description.narrative: In 2019, several evaluations showed progress in the health system, including the baseline study of Child Friendly Communities (CFC), the review of Improved Monitoring for Action and an evaluation of the post distribution of Long-Lasting Insecticidal Nets (LLIN). The findings were used to inform the the design of the next country programme (2020-2024). The evaluations of LLIN distribution revealed the effectiveness and the efficiency of two methods of distribution; community-based and school-based. Operational cost was reduced to $0.9 for the community-based approach and $1.5 for school-based. The MoH scaled up both approaches to other provinces in 2019. | Status:Met | As-of Date:08/02/2020
